{{Top|leg}}
The '''Obroan Institute for [[Archaeology/Legends|Archaeology]]''', often shortened to the '''Obroan Institute''', was a research organization that formed a part of the collection of educational bodies that formed the greater library-world of [[Obroa-skai/Legends|Obroa-skai]]. Devoted to the discovery, analysis, and cataloging of species and civilizations to promote galactic diversity and understanding, the Institute's numerous experts performed both field and desk research, and maintained a fleet of exploration vessels to support the former.

In addition to its headquarters on Obroa-skai, the Institute maintained a major facility on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]], including a landing bay in [[Newport]], and a research base on [[Babali]], and ostensibly operated branches on several other worlds. The Institute was a government-funded segment of the [[New Republic General Ministry|General Ministry]] of the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]], although as a semi-independent institute it operated with relative freedom. Within the Institute, departments like the [[Office of Sentient Species]] managed internal policies. Planets chosen for exploration were selected from a list nominated by member researchers. Each nominated mission required the interested researchers to pursue funding options to finance the expedition from the General Ministry budget or outside sources.

==History==
In [[1 BBY/Legends|1 BBY]], a [[Pre-Republic era|pre-Republic]] specialist at the Institute, Dr. [[Insmot Bowen]], partook in a briefing conference with [[General/Legends|General]] [[Arhul Kurumenga]] of the [[Imperial Department of Military Research/Legends|Imperial Department of Military Research]], [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Conan Antonio Motti/Legends|Conan Antonio Motti]], and [[Master of Imperial Projects]] [[Bevel Lemelisk]], giving a theory about the mysteries of the galaxy, including a [[Western barrier|barrier]] to the west of the Core Worlds, being the result of Celestial technology dating back to the [[Rakatan revolt]], with Motti expressing disbelief at the theory.

In [[17 ABY/Legends|17 ABY]], the Institute was involved in the investigation of [[Brath Qella]] spawned by the pursuit of the [[Teljkon Vagabond]]. The Institute supplied a five-hundred-member research team that investigated the [[Sharu/Legends|Sharu]] of [[Rafa IV]] on behalf of the New Republic.

Later, the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] assault on Obroa-skai left the Institute scrambling to preserve its records and artifacts while fleeing the fallen world. The flight encouraged [[Bel-dar-Nolek]], who had been the director of the Institute since at least 17 ABY, to challenge the New Republic's failure to defend Obroa-skai on the [[New Republic Senate/Legends|Senate]] floor. The director even went so far as to suggest that the Institute to attempt to make peace independently with the Yuuzhan Vong in order to return to Obroa-skai and preserve what data remained.

{{Noncanonstart|legends=1}}
During the spring break of [[Roan Novachez]]'s second year at the [[Jedi academy]] on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]], he took a trip with his friend [[Pasha]] and [[Pasha's father|Pasha's dad]] to their home on Obroa-skai. There, he got to visit Pasha's dad's office at the Obroan Institute for Archaeology. He showed Roan some of the [[Jedi artifact/Legends|Jedi artifacts]] he had been studying, including vintage [[Force crystal]]s, the arm of a [[Tythan|Tythonian]] [[Security droid/Legends|security droid]], the [[Unknown Holocron]], an ancient prototype [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]], a monogrammed [[Ossus Keeper robe]] and an ancient [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] text titled ''[[The Path of the Jedi]]''. Unfortunately, Roan accidentally ripped a page of the book and for the rest of the trip was worried that Pasha's dad was mad at him.
{{Noncanonend}}

